"    CT negative PET positive Paraneoplastic disease",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 432px; height: 276px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    This 71-year-old man presented with a polyneuropathy thought secondary to a paraneoplastic syndrome as he had a high PQ type calcium channel antibody present in serum. PET-CT showing intense metabolic activity in a normal sized left hilar node after CT was negative. Ultrasound guided bronchoscopy sampling revealed small cell lung cancer in this hilar node.",
